{
  "id": 5562829589577728,
  "name": "WebGPU: Transient attachments",
  "summary": "Functionality added to the WebGPU spec after its first shipment in a browser.\n\nA new TRANSIENT_ATTACHMENT GPUTextureUsage lets developers create attachments that allow render pass operations to stay in tile memory, avoiding VRAM traffic and potentially avoiding VRAM allocation for the textures.\n",
